This directory contains demos and tests running on the OpenBDC pod.

Available demos and tests:
+-demo_OpenBDC.dbug12.txt   This is the OpenBDC port of the S12CBase 
|                                demo. It reads SCI input and prints the read 
|                                value in ASCII, hexadecimal, decimal, octal, 
|                                and binary representation. Ctrl-C and CTRL-Z
|                                turn the busy-LED on/off. The following baud
|                                rates are automatically detected:   4800
|                                                                    7200
|                                                                    9600
|                                                                   14400
|                                                                   19200
|                                                                   28800
|                                                                   38400
|                                                                   57600
|                                Baud rate detection  works best by typing the
|                                characters "~" or "@".
|                                This ASCII file contains all D-Bug12 commads to
|                                run the demo in the on-chip RAM. No flashing
|                                required.
|
+-demo_OpenBDC.lst          The assembler listing of the demo code.
